### Description of Change ###
Hi
Now Android scroll view has default 1 second animation. This looks a little bit ugly, when we need scroll only a few points (It moves like a turtle)

Perhaps, it would be OK idea to change 1 sec animation to SmoothScrollTo method (like iOS has)

### API Changes ###

Changed:
 - ScrollView ScrollTo implementation

### Platforms Affected ### 
**Android**

### Behavioral/Visual Changes ###
Now it work like on iOS, in my opinion

### Testing Procedure ###
Here is code for testing, just try to tap buttons and check animation
It won't take 1 second for every scroll

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
	{
		public App ()
		{
			InitializeComponent ();

			var scroll = new ScrollView();

			var st = new StackLayout
			{
				BackgroundColor = Color.Red,
				HeightRequest = 5000,
				Children = {
					new Button
					{
						Text = "Near",
						BackgroundColor = Color.DarkBlue,
						Command = new Command(() => {
							scroll.ScrollToAsync(0, 10, true);
						})
					},
					new Button
					{
						Text = "Far",
						BackgroundColor = Color.DarkBlue,
						Command = new Command(() => {
							scroll.ScrollToAsync(0, 100, true);
						})
					},
					new Button
					{
						Text = "Very far",
						BackgroundColor = Color.DarkBlue,
						Command = new Command(() => {
							scroll.ScrollToAsync(0, 300, true);
						})
					},
					new Button
					{
						Text = "Start",
						BackgroundColor = Color.DarkBlue,
						Command = new Command(() => {
							scroll.ScrollToAsync(0, 0, true);
						})
					},
					new Button
					{
						Text = "Start",
						BackgroundColor = Color.DarkBlue,
						Command = new Command(() => {
							scroll.ScrollToAsync(0, 0, true);
						})
					},
					new Button
					{
						Text = "Start",
						BackgroundColor = Color.DarkBlue,
						Command = new Command(() => {
							scroll.ScrollToAsync(0, 0, true);
						})
					}
				}
			};

			scroll.Content = st;

			MainPage = new ContentPage
			{
				Content = scroll
			};
		}
	}
```
